Pre-Game Insights: Egypt’s national football team will battle for supremacy with the Botswana national football team for the top spot in the Group C AFCON qualifying at the Francistown Stadium.
Botswana doesn’t have any significant status on the international stage, so an easy win for The Pharaohs is expected.
Botswana has struggled recently and lost their opening game of the qualification to Mauritania.
It has been more than 12 years since Botswana has qualified for the African Cup of Nations, with their only appearance in the 2012 edition.
Botswana’s latest defeat saw their winless run extend to four matches.
Egypt’s national football team is the most successful team in the AFCON and is coming off a 3-0 win over Cape Verde in their opening game of the qualifying.
Hossam Hassan’s squad will be hoping to extend their winning run to six matches in the AFCON qualifiers.
Historically, Egypt had the upper hand in their last five meetings against Botswana.
